&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Ophthalmology Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: Ophthalmology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site: Boston&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Training Band 6 with opportunity to progress to band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 1.0 WTE (Full Time)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type: Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new opportunity has arisen for an experienced and highly motivated nurse specialist to join the ophthalmology department with the United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust, based at Lincoln County Hospital, Lincoln with the ability to work at other sites as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an experienced registered nurse in ophthalmic clinical practise, with a proven track record of implementing and delivering quality high standards of nursing care. It is essential that you are pro-active, adaptable and flexible to meet the needs of the service and evidence of leading recent and new initiatives is very desirable. The ability to teach and support junior nursing/medical staff is an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be supported by 6 consultants, 2 speciality doctors, two nurse specialists and 3 core trainees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is a modern clinical area with dedicated fields room, treatment rooms, pre-assessment, minor ops and investigations room. There are specialist nurse-led glaucoma, oculoplastics and post-op clinics and orthoptic-led shared care clinics, along with general and specialist ophthalmic clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The outpatient department is fully equipped for digital fluorescein angiography, digital fundus photography, OCT, pachymetry, Argon and YAG laser photocoagulation, diagnostic B scan ultrasound and biometry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within the outpatient department is a fully staffed orthoptic department which provides services to the outlying hospitals and local authority clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
